metadata.name: fx(word) #40
metadata.description:
"Word" is a single unit of language that has meaning and can be spoken or written.
You can make your favorite word or brief sentence into a work using no more than 10 characters of fx(params).
No matter what language you use or what it means, it's going to turn into a work of art.

--

To highlight the rarity of the params value you set, i have set only text to appear in the feature list.

--

This project is made in 100% pure code with p5js
By Thion, April 2023

metadata.name: Motivational Posters #4
metadata.description:
A tribute to motivational posters you can sometimes find in offices or waiting rooms.

Each planet and star distribution is unique, and comes with its own randomly generated mantra.

Made with p5js and shaders.

Enjoy

metadata.name: AVENUE #111
metadata.description:
Polyphony is the core idea of this work, and it explores that term in digital art using handpicked combinations of colors, angles, shapes, and tension between them in a harmonious way.
Thanks.

metadata.name: Supernova #71
metadata.description:
Inspired by photos taken by the Hubble telescope. Made in p5.js

* Press "s" to alter the color values. (Also when doing resize)
* Press enter to save the current image

The shape can be altered on the following scales:

* Minimal (rare)
* Low
* Medium
* High
* Extreme (rare)

It can be expanded on one of the following scales:

* Low
* Medium
* High

metadata.name: Berkenbos #5
metadata.description:
The catalyst for this project was a code challenge posted on Twitter:

- https://twitter.com/lennyjpg/status/1492708916349833216

Which depicted Gustav Klimt's marvelous "Fir Forest I" painting. This piece is based on that painting and some mints might come close to reproducing the original!

- Be patient. Generating and drawing can take a while!
- Looks best in portrait orientation.

metadata.name: LIQUID #21
metadata.description:
Painting on canvas using feedback, modulations and noises to recreate the idea of an interactive 'liquid show'. Open livemode, activate your webcam and click on the canvas to start the interaction.
The artwork will adjust to your monitor's resolution but still maintain its aspect ratio.

In commemoration of FXHASH's 1 year anniversary.
You can control some parameters of the video input to adjust the effect with:
1 -> Inverts the brightness values
7/8 -> Increases or decreases the limit on the first parameter
+/- -> Increases or decreases the threshold on the second parameter
P' -> Saves a png from canvas

Designed for desktop computers on Google Chrome
Developed with Hydra.js

metadata.name: NWW Sketchbook #17
metadata.description:
Experimental art in honour of the experimental music of Nurse With Wound.

Text comes from the list of various musicians/groups that influenced them, which
appeared in their first album "Chance Meeting on a Dissecting Table of a Sewing Machine and an Umbrella" and was subsequently expanded with their second album, "To the Quiet Men from a Tiny Girl".

Press "s" to save image in a .png file.
